  <p>PAGCOR has settled on a number it likes to repeat: 93.8 percent. That is the share of the 13,399 illegal gambling sites it has flagged to partner agencies that are now blocked &mdash; roughly 12,562 of them. Two months earlier, the figure was about 74 percent. The gap between those two numbers is the story, and so is the strategy the agency has built around it. PAGCOR is not claiming it has won. It is claiming something more modest and more honest: that blocking illegal sites over and over, even knowing they will return, is itself a deterrent worth the effort.</p>

